result.execSummary:
The defendant Skye A. Ashley was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Narcotic Drugs [Modifiers: Second or Subsequent Offense], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(am).
  • Possession of Methamphetamine, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).
  • Bail Jumping-Felony [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

(2:51 PM case called.) Judge Beverly Wickstrom for Branch 3.
All parties and court personnel appear via Zoom. 
Defendant Skye A. Ashley appeared by video from treatment facility. Attorney Zebulon Patek in court for Skye A. Ashley. Prosecuting attorney Tiffany M. Winter in court for the State of Wisconsin.
Agreement has been reached and is recited by counsel.
Defendant waives right to a personal appearance and wants to proceed. Court accepts the defendant's waiver to a personal appearance.
Defendant pleads Guilty to Count 1: Possession of Narcotic Drugs as Second or Subsequent Offense without Repeater, Count 2: Possession of Methamphetamine without Repeater and Count 3: Felony Bail Jumping as Repeater.
Defendant is advised of charges, maximum penalties, elements of the crime(s) and constitutional rights. 
Court accepts the defendant's Guilty pleas and finds the defendant Guilty of Count 1 without Repeater, Count 2 without Repeater and Count 3.
Parties request the Court follow the joint sentencing recommendation.
Defendant makes a statement.

Court withholds sentence and places the defendant on probation for 2 years on Counts 1 and 2 with the following conditions:
180 days jail with Huber privileges, stayed pending further order of the Court on Count 1. AODA and follow through with recommendations and must complete within first 6 months of probation. Maintain absolute sobriety. No contact with E.V., K.N. No contact with any known drug dealers/users, except in a therapeutic setting. Any conditions, programming or treatment per the agent and follow through with recommendations. Provide DNA sample and pay surcharge and pay court costs. Any contraband is ordered destroyed. 123 days credit if probation revoked. Any remaining charges are dismissed and read in. 

Court orders sentence on Count 3 for the defendant to provide DNA sample and pay surcharge and pay court costs. Any remaining charges are dismissed and read in.
